<div>


<h4 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Item 2.02.&nbsp;
Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</font></b></h4>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The information in this Current Report is being
furnished and shall not be deemed &#147;filed&#148; for the purposes of Section&nbsp;18
of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, or otherwise subject to the
liabilities of that Section.&nbsp; The information in this Current Report shall
not be incorporated by reference into any registration statement or other
document pursuant to the Securities Act of 1933, as amended.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On January 31, 2007, Kraft Foods Inc. issued an
earnings release announcing its financial results for the quarter and year
ended December 31, 2006.&nbsp; A copy of the earnings release is attached as
Exhibit&nbsp;99.</font></p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">2</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

on its behalf by the undersigned hereunto duly authorized.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<h1 align="center" style="font-weight:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Kraft Foods Inc. Reports Mixed 2006 Results</font></u></b></h1>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 42.5pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Fourth
quarter reported net revenues decreased 3.0% to $9.4 billion, impacted by one
less week in 2006</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 42.5pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Fourth
quarter reported diluted EPS decreased 17.4% to $0.38; excluding items
affecting comparability, diluted EPS decreased 8.9% to $0.51</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 42.5pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Full-year
reported net revenues increased 0.7% to $34.4 billion, impacted by one less
week in 2006</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 42.5pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Full-year
reported diluted EPS increased 19.4% to $1.85; excluding items affecting
comparability, diluted EPS increased 3.2% to $1.94</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">NORTHFIELD, IL &#150; Jan. 31, 2007 &#150; Kraft Foods Inc.
(NYSE: KFT), a global leader in food and beverages, &#160;today reported that net revenues decreased
3.0% for the fourth quarter 2006 and increased 0.7% for the full-year,
reflecting one less shipping week in 2006 compared to 2005.&#160; Having</font> one less week in 2006 negatively impacted reported net revenues by
approximately 7 percentage points on the quarter and 2 percentage points on the
full year.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;While we&#146;ve made
progress in 2006 on both the top and the bottom lines, the overall turnaround
is not broad-based enough and the foundation for sustainable top-tier performance
is not yet in place. This is likely to continue into the first half of 2007 as
we get the business on a path to predictable growth,&#148; said Irene B. Rosenfeld,
Chief Executive Officer. </font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Commenting on Altria
Group, Inc.&#146;s announced plans to distribute the Kraft Foods Inc. shares it owns
to Altria shareholders, Rosenfeld said, &#147;The forthcoming spin-off from Altria
will provide us with additional tools to enhance our growth.&#160; The new management team is ready for and
looks forward to this exciting next stage in the history of Kraft Foods.&#148;</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Net revenues for the
fourth quarter declined 3.0% to $9.4 billion.&#160;
Excluding a negative 1.7 percentage point impact from divestitures, a
favorable 1.1 percentage point impact from the United Biscuits Iberia
acquisition, and a favorable 1.6 percentage point impact from currency, organic
net revenues</font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font>&#160;decreased 4.0%.&#160; The decline reflected one less shipping week
in 2006.&#160; Strong results were generated
by </p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:7.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font>&#160;The Company&#146;s top-line guidance measure was
redefined in 2006 to be organic net revenues which excludes acquisitions; the
impact of divestitures; currency impact; and asset impairment, exit and
implementation costs.&#160; This measure
differs from the previous ongoing constant currency revenues measure by also
excluding the impact of acquisitions.&#160;
Management believes this measure better reflects revenues on a
go-forward basis and provides improved comparability of results.</p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">1</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='1',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">biscuits, meats, and powdered beverages in North America;
chocolate in EU; and by many categories in Latin America and Eastern Europe.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Product mix improved
across all segments, contributing 2.0 percentage points to organic net revenue
growth, including gains in sugar-free <i>Crystal
Light</i> powdered beverages and strong growth in developing
markets.&#160; Pricing added 0.3 percentage
points to revenue growth and included increases in Latin America, Eastern
Europe, and cereals in North America that were partially offset by lower prices
related to dairy costs in North America Cheese &amp; Foodservice and increased
promotional spending in European coffee.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Total ongoing volume
declined 4.4%, reflecting the estimated 7 percentage point impact of one less
week in 2006 partially offset by 2 percentage points from the UB Iberia acquisition.&#160; A number of products performed well,
including </font><i>Oscar Mayer</i><b>&nbsp;</b>meats and <i>Nabisco</i> cookies
and snack crackers in North America, <i>Milka</i>
chocolate in the EU, <i>Jacobs</i>
soluble coffee in Russia and Ukraine, and <i>Lacta</i>
chocolate in Brazil.&#160; Gains by
these products were partially offset by product item pruning and the
discontinuation of select product lines, primarily in North America Foodservice
and in the Canadian ready-to-drink beverage business, as well as by share
declines in <i>Maxwell House</i> coffee,
<i>Kraft</i> salad dressings and <i>Planters</i> snack nuts.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Items Affecting Diluted EPS
Comparability</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">*Does
not add due to rounding</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the quarter, the
Company incurred $491 million ($319 million after-tax or $0.20 per diluted
share) in asset impairment, exit and implementation costs, including the
previously disclosed $245 million write-</font></p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">2</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='2',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">down of <i>Tassimo</i>
assets, $177 million of costs for streamlining programs and the $69 million
write-down of <i>Cream Of Wheat</i>
brand and assets in connection with the recently announced sale.&#160; For comparison, in the fourth quarter 2005,
the Company incurred $300 million ($162 million after-tax or $0.10 per diluted
share) in asset impairment, exit and implementation costs.&#160; Also, in the fourth quarter of 2006, the
Company recorded a gain on the sale of its <i>Minute
Rice</i> brand and assets of $226 million, partially offset by a $95
million loss on the sale of a coffee manufacturing facility.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Fourth quarter operating
income decreased 18.6% from the prior year to $974 million.&#160; Excluding asset impairment, exit and
implementation costs and gains/losses on the sale of businesses, operating
income decreased 11.3% and operating income margin decreased to 14.2% in 2006
from 15.6% in 2005.&#160; The margin decline
was primarily due to higher investments in marketing and in research and
development.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company&#146;s tax
rate in the fourth quarter 2006 was 25.7%.&#160;
Excluding the tax effects of asset impairment, exit and implementation
costs and gains/losses on the sales of businesses, the effective tax rate in
the fourth quarter 2006 was 29.8%.&#160; This
compares to an effective tax rate of 30.3% in the fourth quarter last year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Fourth quarter 2006
reported net earnings were $624 million, a decrease of 19.3% versus last year,
while reported diluted earnings per share were $0.38, down 17.4% from $0.46
last year.&#160; Excluding asset impairment,
exit and implementation costs as well as the gains/losses on the sale of
businesses, net earnings for the quarter declined 11.0% and diluted earnings
per share decreased 8.9% to $0.51, primarily reflecting the estimated impact of
one less week on earnings per share of approximately $0.04. The remaining
change includes the operating income decline caused primarily by the higher
investment in marketing and in research and development, partially offset by
the benefit of the Company&#146;s stock repurchase program.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Full-year 2006 reported
net earnings were $3.1 billion, an increase of 16.3% versus last year, while
reported diluted earnings per share were $1.85, up 19.4% from $1.55 last
year.&#160; Excluding items affecting
comparability, diluted earnings per share increased 3.2% to $1.94, reflecting
higher operating income and the benefit of the Company&#146;s stock repurchase
program, partially offset by higher taxes and the impact of one less week.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Kraft Foods
continues to make progress on its previously announced cost restructuring
program.&#160; In 2006, the Company announced nine
facility closures/sales and implemented overhead reduction programs.&#160; By the end of the fourth quarter, annualized
ongoing savings for the program to date totaled approximately $540 million, up
from approximately $260 million at the end of 2005.&#160; The cost of the program in 2006 was </font></p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">3</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='3',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$673 million. These costs
exclude the sale of a coffee manufacturing facility, previously targeted for
closure, which is now accounted for as a loss on sale.&#160; Other asset impairments for 2006 totaled $424
million and included the write-down for <i>Tassimo</i>
and impairments for the sales of <i>Milk-Bone</i>
and <i>Cream of Wheat</i>.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Since the
inception of its cost restructuring program in 2004, the Company has incurred
total costs of $1.6 billion.&#160; The Company
now expects total costs for the full program to be $3.0 billion, down from a
previous expectation of $3.7 billion.&#160;
Additionally, cumulative savings for the total program are expected to
reach approximately $1.0&nbsp;billion, approximately $0.1 billion less than the
previous expectation. These changes reflect revisions to planned activities and
lower-than-expected costs for several initiatives. The updated components of
the program are as follows:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:6.0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Full-year discretionary cash flow</font><font size="1" style="font-size:7.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font>&#160;plus divestiture
proceeds was $3.5 billion, down $0.5 billion from 2005. The decrease primarily
reflects lower proceeds from the sales of businesses in 2006.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the quarter, the Company repurchased
8.9 million Class A shares at a total cost of $313 million, bringing 2006 share
repurchases to 38.7 million Class A shares at a total cost of $1.25
billion.&#160; As of December 31, 2006, $1.0
billion remained under the Company&#146;s $2.0 billion share repurchase plan.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Kraft
Spin-off</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As separately
communicated, Altria Group, Inc. will distribute its ownership in Kraft Foods
Inc. to Altria shareholders.&#160; As a result
of this distribution, the Company will lose the benefit of its tax
consolidation within the Altria Group, Inc., and expects its effective tax rate
to increase to approximately 37% by 2008.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Additionally Altria Group,
Inc. employee stock options will be split into adjusted Altria Group, Inc. and
Kraft Foods Inc. stock options.&#160; This
will cause the number of Kraft Foods Inc. diluted shares outstanding to
increase.&#160; Based on current forecasts,
the Company expects a dilutive impact on earnings per share of approximately
$0.02 on an annual basis.&#160; Administrative
services provided by Altria Group, Inc. will be sourced internally or through
third parties at similar costs.</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:7.0pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font>&#160;The company defines discretionary cash flow as
net cash provided by operating activities less capital expenditures, and
utilizes this measure for its cash flow guidance because it believes it more
fully reflects both ongoing cash generation and usage activities. Discretionary
cash flow is available to finance acquisitions, repay maturing debt, and
distribute to shareholders.</p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">4</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='4',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2007 Outlook<a name="a2007Outlook_004137"></a></font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company expects to
issue EPS guidance for 2007 on February 20 during its business plan
presentation at the Consumer Analysts Group of New York conference.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Three items that
will impact year-to-year comparisons are the expected tax rate, divestitures
and the split of employee stock options. The Company expects its full-year
effective tax rate to average 35.5% in 2007 (up from 31.7% in 2006), excluding
the impact of charges for asset impairment, exit and implementation costs, and
one-time gains and losses related to acquisitions and divestitures. Previously
completed divestitures and the announced sale of <i>Cream of
Wheat</i> will impact 2007 EPS by $0.03 compared to the prior year. The
split of employee stock options will increase diluted shares outstanding and
reduce diluted earnings per share as referenced above.</font></p>

<p style="font-weight:bold;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Results by Segment<a name="ResultsBySegment_004152"></a></font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following results by
segment are presented in the manner described in the business segment reporting
structure discussion in the Company&#146;s Form 8-K filing dated March 27,
2006.&#160; Reported operating companies
income (OCI) is defined as operating income before corporate expenses and
amortization of intangibles.&#160; Management
believes this measure helps investors analyze business segment performance and trends.&#160; For a reconciliation of OCI to operating
income, see Schedules 1 and 6 of the attached financial schedules.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Summary
of Reported Results By Segment</font></u></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(percent change from
prior year)</font></p>

 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">5</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following table
presents the 2006 segment growth rates on an ongoing basis, which excludes the
impact of divestitures; asset impairment, exit and implementation costs; and
gains/losses on the sale of businesses.&#160;
Also presented is organic net revenue growth, which excludes
acquisitions; the impact of divestitures; currency impact; and asset impairment,
exit and implementation costs.&#160; Adjusted
organic net revenue growth is also presented, which excludes the impact of one
less shipping week in 2006 than 2005 from organic net revenues. The Company
estimates that this week represents an approximate 7&nbsp;percentage point
decline on the quarter and a 2&nbsp;percentage point decline on the full year. Further
information on the impact of these items, including reference to comparable
GAAP measures, is included in the attached financial schedules.&#160; A quantitative reconciliation of all non-GAAP
measures used in this fourth quarter 2006 earnings release can be found in the
Investors section of www.kraft.com by clicking on &#147;Financial News and Events,&#148;
then &#147;Financial News Releases.&#148;</font></p>

of Ongoing, Organic, and Adjusted Organic Results By Segment</font></u></b></p>

prior year)</font></p>

  <td width="16" valign="bottom" style="padding:0pt .7pt 0pt 0pt;width:12.0pt;">

  </td>

  </td>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 16.95pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">*Excludes the impact of one less shipping week
in 2006 than 2005.&#160; The company estimates
that this week represents an approximate 7 percentage point decline on the
quarter and a 2 percentage point decline on the full year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">North America Beverages</font></u></i></b> reported a decrease in net revenues for the
fourth quarter of 6.7% to $743 million, with organic net revenue down 6.9%,
reflecting one less week in 2006, lower volume and improved product mix.&#160; Key strength in the segment included
convenient and better-for-you powdered beverages such as <i>Crystal Light</i> On-The-Go.&#160; Other contributors
were ready-to-drink beverages, driven by <i>Capri
Sun Roarin&#146; Waters</i>, and premium offerings in coffee, including <i>Starbucks</i> and <i>Gevalia</i>.&#160;
These successes were offset by
share losses in <i>Maxwell House</i>
coffee, due to competitive pressures and a difficult prior year comparison,
and the discontinuation of certain ready-to-drink lines.&#160; Reported OCI was a loss of $140 million,
which included the $95 million loss on the sale of a coffee manufacturing
facility and $72 million in incremental asset impairment, implementation and
exit costs, primarily related to the </p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">6</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='6',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">write-down
of <i>Tassimo</i> assets.&#160; Ongoing OCI was down 51.2% reflecting one
less week in 2006 and higher input costs, including green coffee, packaging and
sugar and higher overheads.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">North America Cheese &amp; Foodservice</font></u></i></b> reported net revenues were down 7.7% to
$1.67 billion.&#160; Organic net revenues
declined 7.8% reflecting one less week in 2006, lower pricing related to
declines in dairy costs and the discontinuation of lower margin product lines
in the Foodservice business.&#160; Successes
in the quarter included natural cheese, driven by convenient <i>Kraft</i> natural snack cheeses, and grated cheese,
including the introduction of <i>Grate-It-Fresh</i>
parmesan cheese.&#160; These were offset by
category and share declines for <i>Velveeta</i>
process cheese.&#160; Reported OCI was down
2.2% to $271 million including an $11 million increase in asset impairment,
implementation and exit costs.&#160; Ongoing
OCI grew 1.8% as lower dairy costs more than offset lower prices and one less
week in 2006.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">North America Convenient Meals</font></u></i></b> reported a decline in net revenues of 5.9%,
to $1.19 billion, with an organic net revenue decrease of 4.7%, reflecting one
less week in 2006.&#160; Positive drivers
included favorable product mix and continued volume gains from new convenience
products.&#160; Revenue performance in meats continued to be driven by market share
gains from <i>Oscar Mayer Deli Fresh</i>,
hot dogs, and bacon.&#160; Momentum continued
in the <i>California Pizza Kitchen</i>
line, now a $100 million business, including the new crispy thin crust pizza.&#160; Reported
OCI grew 62.4% to $346 million due to a $226 million gain on the sale of the <i>Minute Rice</i> brand and assets.&#160; Ongoing OCI decreased 29.8% driven by the
impact of one less week in 2006, higher input costs (LIFO) and investments in
quality, capacity and marketing initiatives.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">North America </font></u></i></b><b><i><u style="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Grocery</u></i></b> reported net revenues declined 14.1% to $712
million including an 8.3 percentage point impact from divestitures.&#160; Organic net revenues were down 6.7%,
reflecting one less week in 2006.&#160;
Successes in select convenient and better-for-you offerings such as <i>Jell-O</i> sugar-free ready-to-eat pudding and
sugar-free <i>Cool Whip</i> topping were
offset by category weakness and share declines in <i>Kraft</i> salad dressings and category weakness in <i>Jell-O</i> dry packaged desserts.&#160; Reported OCI more than doubled to $245
million primarily due to $124 million of lower asset impairment, implementation
and exit costs.&#160; Ongoing OCI grew 3.3% as
lower overheads were partially offset by lower volumes primarily reflecting one
less week in 2006.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">North America </font></u></i></b><b><i><u style="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Snacks
&amp; Cereals</u></i></b>
reported net revenues fell 6.6% to $1.63 billion including a negative 3.4
percentage point impact from the divestiture of the <i>Milk Bone </i>pet snacks brand and assets.&#160; </p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">7</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='7',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Organic
net revenues declined 3.6% reflecting one less week in 2006, partially offset
by higher cereals pricing.&#160; Cookie
performance delivered share and category growth with successes in the <i>Oreo, Chips Ahoy!</i>, <i>Nilla</i> and <i>Newtons</i>
cookie franchises. Crackers results included strong growth in <i>Triscuit, Honey Maid </i>and new varieties in
toasted chips, partially offset by weakness in <i>Kraft</i>
<i>Cheese Nips</i> and <i>Ritz Bits s</i>andwiches.&#160; Cereals revenues reflected the success of the
new <i>Grape Nuts Trail Mix Crunch</i>
cereal and ongoing momentum of <i>Post Honey
Bunches of Oats,</i> partially offset by lower revenues in kids&#146;
cereals.&#160; <i>Planters</i> snack nut revenues declined due to market share
loss to out-of-aisle competition. Reported OCI was down 32.1% to $163 million
due to $26 million of higher asset impairment, implementation and exit costs,
including the<i> Cream of Wheat</i>
impairment, and the absence of $26 million in income from divested operations versus
the prior year.&#160; Ongoing OCI decreased
9.1% reflecting one less week in 2006 and investments in quality and growth
initiatives plus higher commodity costs, partially offset by higher prices and
productivity.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">European Union</font></u></i></b> reported net revenues grew 5.5% to $2.12
billion, with 5.4 points contributed by the acquisition of United Biscuits
Iberia.&#160; Organic net revenue growth
decreased 4.6% due to one less week in 2006.&#160;
Chocolate revenues reflected solid results across most markets behind
new product introductions, such as <i>Milka
Tendres Moments</i>, and stepped up marketing support.&#160; In Coffee, increased price promotion and
marketing support helped stabilize the base business while <i>Tassimo</i> continued to grow.&#160; Reported OCI was a loss of $14 million due to
$185 million in higher asset impairment, implementation and exit costs versus
the prior year, primarily due to the write-down in <i>Tassimo</i> assets.&#160;
Ongoing OCI decreased 8.5% due to one less week in 2006 and higher
investment in the coffee business.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><b><i><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Developing Markets, Oceania &amp;
North Asia</font></u></i></b>&nbsp;reported
net revenues grew 8.0% to $1.31
billion, or 6.2% on an organic basis, despite one less week in 2006.&#160; The strong performance was led by growth in Eastern
Europe, Middle East &amp; Africa (EEMA) and in Latin America.&#160; In
EEMA, revenues were driven by coffee and chocolate in Russia, Ukraine, Romania,
and Bulgaria.&#160; Revenue growth continued
to be strong in Russia and Ukraine, with higher volumes, favorable product mix
from gains in <i>Jacobs</i> and <i>Carte Noire</i> soluble coffee, and the benefit of
pricing.&#160; In Latin America, strong
revenue growth was driven by the benefit of pricing and positive mix.&#160; Gains were concentrated in chocolate,
biscuits and refreshment beverages.&#160; In
Asia Pacific, improvements in biscuits and beverages in China were offset by
volume declines in cheese in Australia.&#160; Reported
OCI grew 16.7% to $161 million
reflecting in part the positive impact of a $6 million loss on sales of an
asset in 2005.&#160; Ongoing OCI was up 13.0%
as the benefit of the strong revenue growth was partially offset by incremental
investments in marketing and infrastructure and the impact of one less week in
2006.</p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; *&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
*</font></p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">8</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<p style="line-height:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Kraft Foods will host a
conference call for members of the investment community to review its results
at 4 p.m. ET on January 31, 2007.&#160; Access
to a live audio webcast is available at www.kraft.com and a replay of the
conference call will be available on the Company&#146;s web site.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="line-height:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Forward-Looking
Statements</font></u></b></p>

<h3 style="font-weight:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This
press release contains projections of future results and other forward-looking
statements.&#160; One can identify these
forward-looking statements by use of words such as &#147;strategy,&#148; &#147;expects,&#148;
&#147;plans,&#148; &#147;anticipates,&#148; &#147;believes,&#148; &#147;will,&#148; &#147;continues,&#148; &#147;estimates,&#148; &#147;intends,&#148;
&#147;projects,&#148; &#147;goals,&#148; &#147;targets&#148; and other words of similar meaning.&#160; One can also identify them by the fact that
they do not relate strictly to historical or current facts. These statements
are based on the Company&#146;s current assumptions and estimates and are subject to
risks and uncertainties. In connection with the &#147;safe harbor&#148; provisions of the
Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995, the Company is hereby
identifying important factors that could cause actual results and outcomes to
differ materially from those contained in any forward looking statement made by
or on behalf of the Company.&#160; These
factors include: (a) the effect on the Company of competition in its markets,
changes in consumer preferences and demand for its products, including diet
trends, changing prices for its raw materials and local economic and market
conditions; (b) the Company&#146;s continued ability to promote brand equity
successfully, to anticipate and respond to new consumer trends, to develop new
products and markets, to broaden brand portfolios, to compete effectively with
lower priced products in a consolidating environment at the retail and
manufacturing levels and to improve productivity; (c) the Company&#146;s ability to
consummate and successfully integrate acquisitions and to realize the cost
savings and improved asset utilization contemplated by its restructuring
program; (d) the impact of gains or losses, or lost operating income, from the
sales of businesses that are less of a strategic fit within the Company&#146;s
portfolio; (e) the effects of foreign economies, changes in tax requirements
and currency movements; (f) fluctuations in levels of customer inventories and
credit and other business risks related to the operations of the Company&#146;s
customers; (g) the Company&#146;s access to credit markets, borrowing costs and
credit ratings; (h) the Company&#146;s benefit expense, which is subject to the
investment performance of pension plan assets, interest rates and cost
increases for medical benefits offered to employees and retirees; (i) the
impact of recalls if products become adulterated or misbranded, liability if
product consumption causes injury, ingredient disclosure and labeling laws and
regulations, potential claims relating to false or deceptive advertising under
consumer protection or other laws and the possibility that consumers could lose
confidence in the safety and quality of certain food products; (j) consumer
concerns regarding genetically modified organisms and the health implications
of obesity and trans fatty acids; and (k) potential short-term volatility in
the </font></h3>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Non-GAAP Financial Measures</font></u></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt;">The Company reports its
financial results in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles
(GAAP).&#160; Management believes that certain
non-GAAP measures and corresponding ratios that it uses to manage the business
provide additional meaningful comparisons between current results and results
in prior operating periods.&#160; More
specifically, management believes these non-GAAP measures reflect fundamental
business performance because they exclude certain items that affect
comparability of results.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt;">The non-GAAP measures that the
Company is using to present operating results exclude certain items, such as
asset impairment, exit and implementation costs primarily related to a
restructuring program that began in the fourth quarter of 2004 (the
&#147;Restructuring Program&#148;).&#160; These
restructuring charges include separation-related costs, asset write-downs, and
other costs related to the implementation of the Restructuring Program.&#160; Other excluded items pertain to the impact of
divested businesses; asset impairment charges on certain long-lived assets;
gains and losses on the sales of businesses; the favorable resolution of Altria
Group, Inc.&#146;s 1996-1999 IRS Tax Audit in 2006; and earnings from discontinued
operations in 2005.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt;">The Company also uses organic
net revenues and operating companies income (OCI) and corresponding growth
ratios as non-GAAP measures.&#160; Organic net
revenues is defined as net revenues excluding acquisitions; the impact of
divestitures; currency impact; and asset impairment, exit and implementation
costs.&#160; Management believes this measure
better reflects revenues on a go-forward basis and provides improved comparability
of results.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;text-indent:36.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt;">Reported operating companies
income (OCI) is defined as operating income before corporate expenses and
amortization of intangibles.&#160; Management
uses ongoing OCI to evaluate segment performance and allocate resources.&#160; Ongoing OCI at a segment level excludes the
impact of divestitures; asset impairment, exit and implementation costs; and
gains/losses on the sales of businesses.&#160;
Management </font></p>


 <p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:24.0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font face="Times New Roman">10</font></p> <br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='10',FILE='C:\fc\31105426648_D10466_1658793\3021-1-mm-01.htm',USER='jmsproofassembler',CD='Jan 31 10:54 2007' -->
<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">



<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt;">believes this measure helps investors analyze
business segment performance and trends.&#160;
Ongoing OCI on a total Company (consolidated) basis does not exclude the
impact of divestitures.</font></p>

supplemental financial data and corresponding reconciliations to GAAP financial
measures for the quarter and twelve months ended December 31, 2006, and
December 31, 2005.&#160; Non-GAAP financial
measures should be viewed in addition to, and not as an alternative for, the
Company&#146;s reported results prepared in accordance with GAAP.&#160; In addition, the non-GAAP measures the
Company is using may differ from non-GAAP measures that other companies use.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Includes
implementation costs of $1 in 2005</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Includes
implementation costs of $12 in 2006 and $22 in 2005</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(c)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Includes implementation
costs of $30 in 2006 and $3 in 2005</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The
company&#146;s fourth quarter results include one less shipping week in 2006 than
2005. The company estimates that this week represents an approximate 7 pp. of
revenue and operating income decline on the quarter.</p>

2005. The company estimates that this week represents an approximate 7 pp. of
operating income decline on the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>2005 results have been restated for the new segment structure.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company&#146;s fourth quarter results include one less shipping week in
2006 than 2005. The company estimates that this week represents an approximate
7 pp. of volume decline on the quarter.</font></p>

<br><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="center">

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>2005 results have been restated for the new segment structure.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company&#146;s fourth quarter results include one less shipping week in
2006 than 2005. The company estimates that this week represents an approximate
7 pp. of revenue decline on the quarter.</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>2005 results have been restated for the new segment structure.</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company&#146;s fourth quarter results include one less shipping week in
2006 than 2005. The company estimates that this week represents an approximate
7 pp. of operating companies income decline on the quarter.</font></p>

<p style="line-height:1.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Includes
implementation costs of $2 in 2005</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Includes
implementation costs of $25 in 2006 and $56 in 2005</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt 12.0pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(c)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Includes implementation
costs of $70 in 2006 and $29 in 2005</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The
company&#146;s full year results include one less shipping week in 2006 than 2005.
The company estimates that this week represents an approximate 2 pp. of revenue
and operating income decline on the full year.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(**)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160; </font>Basic
and diluted earnings per share are computed for each of the periods presented. Accordingly,
the sum of the quarterly earnings per share amounts may not agree to the
year-to-date amounts.</p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The
company&#146;s full year results include one less shipping week in 2006 than 2005. </p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 36.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company estimates that this week represents an
approximate 2 pp. of operating income decline on the full year.</font></p>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10.0pt;margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 18.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(**)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160; </font>Basic
and diluted earnings per share are computed for each of the periods presented. </p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt 36.0pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:-18.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Accordingly, the sum of the quarterly earnings per
share amounts may not agree to the year-to-date amounts.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)
2005 results have been restated for the new segment structure.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company&#146;s full year results include one less shipping week in 2006
than 2005.&#160; The company estimates that
this week represents an approximate 2 pp. of volume decline on the full year.</font></p>

<div style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><hr size="1" width="160" noshade color="black" align="left" style="width:120.0pt;"></div>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(*)
2005 results have been restated for the new segment structure.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company&#146;s full year results include one less shipping week in 2006
than 2005.&#160; The company estimates that
this week represents an approximate 2 pp. of revenue decline on the full year.</font></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:right;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Schedule 10</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">KRAFT FOODS INC.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">and Subsidiaries</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Operating Companies Income by
Business Segments</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">For the
Years Ended December 31, (*)</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">($ in millions)</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Unaudited)</font></p>

2005 results have been restated for the new segment structure.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0pt 0pt .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The company&#146;s full year
results include one less shipping week in 2006 than 2005.&#160; The company estimates that this week
represents an approximate 2 pp. of operating companies income decline on the
full year.</font></p>
